   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-20_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1816-05-20">May 20, 1816</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                  My dear
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>.
                     Miles</persName> 
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I should be much<lb/>
               obliged to you if you<lb/>
               could buy for me a<lb/>
               yard &amp; half of thin <hi rend="underline">fine</hi>
               <lb/>
               clear <del>muslin</del> India<lb/>
               muslin for morning<lb/>
               handkerchiefs &amp; borders<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>- I should wish to have<lb/>
               it finer and <hi rend="underline">clearer</hi>
               <lb/>
               than the last you were<lb/>
               so good to get for me<lb/>
               &amp; I should not think<lb/>
               15 or 16 shillings too high<lb/>
               a price for what would<lb/>
               be really good - There<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-20_page02.jpg"/>
               is a kind of muslin which<lb/>
               is not so thick as Jaconette<lb/>
               nor so thin as buck<lb/>
               muslin I believe it<lb/>
               is called <hi rend="underline">Mull</hi> &amp; this<lb/>
               is the kind I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. prefer<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I am not in any<lb/>
               hurry therefore pray<lb/>
               do not inconvenience<lb/>
               yourself as to <hi rend="underline">time</hi>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p> Whenever you have<lb/>
               bought it send it over<lb/>
               as you did <del>befo</del> the last<lb/>
               between the leaves of any<lb/>
               book or pamphlet.<lb/>
               Which <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1" cert="high">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.
                  Miles</persName>  may<lb/>
               recommend &amp; direct<lb/> 
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-20_page03.jpg"/>
               - 1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>. cover to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss <choice><orig>E.</orig><reg>Edgeworth</reg></choice></persName>
               <lb/>
               2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> cover to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#FoxC1">CJ Fox Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></persName>
               
               <lb/>
               3 cover to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#TaylW1">W Taylor Esq</persName>
               <lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin-Castle_IE">Castle Dublin</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I hope you will be<lb/>
               able to send me a<lb/>
               good account of<lb/>
               your own &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles's</persName>
               <lb/>
               health - I have the<lb/>
               pleasure to tell you<lb/>
               that my <persName ref="Personography.xml#EdgeR1">father's</persName> is<lb/>
               wonderfully recovered<lb/>
               - within this last month<lb/>
               - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">He</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. E</persName> are in<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName> &amp; will be there<lb/>
               a few days - my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">father</persName>
               <lb/>
               is still trying <choice><orig>Exp<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi></orig><reg>Experiments</reg></choice> on<lb/>
               wheel carriages - I wish<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles</persName> would sometimes<lb/>
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-20_page04.jpg"/>
               write to me - I always like<lb/>
               to hear from him <lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I enclose a<add>
                  <hi rend="underline">note</hi>
               </add>
               <del>draft</del> on Hoare<lb/>
               to him for £5 - with this I beg<lb/>
               you to pay for the muslin<lb/>
               <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1816-05-20_page01.jpg"/>
               and<lb/>
               to pay<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntR1" cert="medium">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                  <lb/>
                  Hunter</persName>
               <lb/>
               for any<lb/>
               muslin<lb/>
               &amp; lace<lb/>
               he may<lb/>
               have<lb/>
               paid<lb/>
               you<lb/>
               for<lb/>
               that no<lb/>
               such<lb/>
               articles<lb/>
               may<lb/>
               appear<lb/>
               in his<lb/>
               accounts<lb/>
               against<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">ME</persName>
               20 May 1816   
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p/>
            </postscript>
